Package uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.parquetstore.operation.handler.utilities

Utilities used to implement the core operations for the Parquet store.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AggregateAndSortData
    Aggregates and sorts the data in a list of files into one sorted file.
    AggregateDataForGroup
    Aggregates data in Parquet files from one group.
    AggregateGafferRowsFunction
    This is used by the Spark reduceByKey method to aggregate two GenericRowWithSchemas using the Gaffer aggregators.
    CalculatePartitioner
    Calculates the GraphPartitioner from a snapshot directory containing all the Parquet files for a graph.
    ExtractKeyFromRow
    This class is used to extract the key from each Row using the set of groupBy column names.
    ParquetElementRetriever
    Converts the inputs for get element operations to a mapping of files to Parquet filters which is then looped over to retrieve the filtered Elements.
    RetrieveElementsFromFile
    Used to retrieve the elements from a single file and put the elements into a shared ConcurrentLinkedQueue.
    SeqObjectPartitioner  
    SortFullGroup
    This class is used to sort the data for a single group by loading in the /aggregate folder within a group.
    SortFullGroup.SeqComparator  
    SortGroupSplit
    This class is used to sort the data for a single split of a group by loading in the /aggregate/split folder within a group.
    WriteUnsortedData
    Takes an Iterable of Elements and writes the elements out into Parquet files split into directories for each group.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CallableResult
